/-- A continuous additive map between two vector spaces over `ℝ` is `ℝ`-linear. -/
theorem map_real_smul {G} [AddMonoidHomClass G E F] (f : G) (hf : continuous f) (c : exprℝ) (x : E) :
    f («expr • » c x) = «expr • » c (f x) :=
  suffices (fun c : exprℝ => f («expr • » c x)) = fun c : exprℝ => «expr • » c (f x) from _root_.congr_fun this c
  rat.dense_embedding_coe_real.dense.equalizer (hf.comp <| continuous_id.smul continuous_const)
    (continuous_id.smul continuous_const) (funext fun r => map_rat_cast_smul f (exprℝ) (exprℝ) r x)
#align map_real_smul map_real_smul
